text:
Chynybaĭ Tursunbekov (15 October 1960 – 7 July 2020) was a Kyrgyz Social Democratic Party politician. He was a member of the Supreme Council from 2010 until his death. Between 2016 to 2017, he was President of the Supreme Council. He was born in Jalan-Bulak, Kirghiz SSR.
Tursunbekov died on 7 July 2020 from pneumonia caused by COVID-19 in Bishkek, Kyrgyzstan at the age of 59.
